@Node "Shortcut"
@Prev "Instructions"
@Next "Instructions"
@Toc "Main"
@Title "What about those shortcuts ???"

Shortcut.

For Gadgets : Just press the letter with the underscore, for the desired option.

For Menus   : As usual 'Right Amiga key' and 'letter', simultaneously.

For Navigation buttons : Press 'Left' or 'Right' arrow keys.

For Home & Eof gadgets, press Right_Shift and Left or Right arrow key.

Neither are case sensitive.

@Endnode

@Node "Limitations"
@Toc "Main"
@Title "GetSDat limitations and bugs"

Limitations and bugs.

You cannot use more than the first nine fields of a database, this limit may
change in future versions.

The program cannot detach itself from the cli. I will try to figure out why. For
the moment, it can safely be installed in programs like 'Toolsdaemon', by Nico
François if you specify the entry, as a '(CLI)' entry, or you can run it <NIL:
>NIL:.

All database files including exported '#?.asc' files MUST reside in the 'Sbase4:'
assign.

All '@{"#?.GetSDatConfig" LINK "ConfigFiles"}' files must be in 's:'

Some national characters doesn't seem to be supported by SBase4. If this ever
changes I will implement support for them in GetSDat.

If you find any bugs, then contact the @{"author" Link "Kastor Lieberung"}

@EndNode

