@Node "Update"

If you are using a version of GetSDat prior to 38.100, it is neccesary to remake
your @{"configuration files" Link "ConfigFiles"}, this is easily done. @{"Clicking in this gadget" SYSTEM "delete s:#?.GetSDatCFG"} will
delete all .GetSDatCfg files from your 's:' dir. After that, follow the normal
procedure to @{"install" Link "Install"} GetSdat configuration files again

@EndNode
